<subSubSection pageId="9" pageNumber="48" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,500]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,223,248]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A species of 
<taxonomicName box="[483,628,224,248]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Blenniidae" genus="Meiacanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[483,628,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Meiacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(subgenus 
<taxonomicName box="[760,905,224,248]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Blenniidae" genus="Meiacanthus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[760,905,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Meiacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) with major portion of dentary gland dorsally positioned and held in place laterally by dorsolateral flange of dentary; dorsal fin IV, 
<number box="[1096,1127,260,284]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="24.0">24</number>
; color pattern characterized by two mid-lateral dark stripes, and dorsal fin with a dark submarginal stripe and about 
<number box="[1133,1161,295,319]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="10.0">10</number>
dark proximal blotches.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="10" lastPageNumber="49" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="9.[151,1437,151,500]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,345,331,356]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48">Description.</emphasis>
Dorsal fin IV, 
<number box="[512,543,332,356]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="24.0">24</number>
. Anal fin II, 
<number box="[687,718,332,356]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="14.0">14</number>
. Pectoral fin 
<number box="[867,897,332,356]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="14.0">14</number>
- 
<number box="[906,936,332,356]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="14.0">14</number>
. Caudal fin: procurrent rays 
<number box="[1257,1271,332,356]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="5.0">5</number>
+ 
<number box="[1289,1303,332,356]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="5.0">5</number>
; segmented rays 
<number box="[205,234,367,391]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="11.0">11</number>
, inner rays not elongated or deeply incised. Vertebrae: precaudal 
<number box="[969,997,367,391]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="13.0">13</number>
+ caudal 
<number box="[1108,1139,367,391]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="20.0">20</number>
. A pair of canines posteriorly in each jaw, those in lower jaw very large with a deep frontal groove; incisor teeth 
<quantity box="[1126,1183,404,428]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.064" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" unit="in" value="16.0">16 in</quantity>
lower and upper jaws. Lateral line present, terminating below 
<number box="[609,622,439,463]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="5.0">5</number>
th dorsal-fin ray; mandibular and posttemporal pores 
<number box="[1244,1260,439,463]" pageId="9" pageNumber="48" value="3.0">3</number>
; single median supratemporal pore.
</paragraph>
